# Sumit API - Key schemas for payment canary

## multivendorcharge Request Schema
`OfficeGuy.Apps.Billing.MVC.API.PaymentsController_Payments_MultiVendorCharge_Request`

Required fields: Credentials, Customer, Items

- Customer: `Accounting_Typed_Customer` (same shared schema across ALL endpoints)
  - SearchMode: "Automatic (0)", "None (1)", "ExternalIdentifier (2)", "Name (3)", "CompanyNumber (4)", "Phone (5)", "EmailAddress (6)"
  - ID, Name, EmailAddress, Phone, etc.
- PaymentMethod: `PaymentMethod` (nullable) - "Leave this empty to use the customer payment method, or when using the SingleUseToken"
  - CreditCard_Token, CreditCard_Number, Type, etc.
- SingleUseToken: nullable string
- Items: MultiVendorChargeItem[] (includes CompanyID + APIKey per vendor item)

## Key insight from PaymentMethod description:
> "Leave this empty to use the customer payment method, or when using the SingleUseToken"

This means: if PaymentMethod is null AND SingleUseToken is null, Sumit uses the CUSTOMER'S saved payment method.

## Customer SearchMode enum:
- Automatic (0) - search by name/email/phone automatically  
- None (1) - search by ID
- ExternalIdentifier (2)
- Name (3)
- CompanyNumber (4)
- Phone (5)
- EmailAddress (6)

NOTE: SearchMode "None (1)" means lookup by ID, NOT "no search". This is DIFFERENT from what we assumed!
